Vant API (1.0.0)

Download OpenAPI specification:Download

live

Process realtime conditions

Processes realtime conditions from the weather station. The api processes the data in multiple ways (e.g. to update the highs and lows or to create a new record). One have to use the configured units. The used api key needs write access.

Authorizations:
api_key
Request Body schema: application/json

Get all realtime conditions

Gets the latest processed realtime conditions (and the some extra realtime information fetched from the meteomatics api). They are automatically converted into the desired units. If no units are passed the configured default units will be used. Your api key needs read access.

Authorizations:
api_key
query Parameters
rain
string (RainUnit)
Enum: "in" "mm"

The desired rain unit.

wind
string (WindUnit)
Enum: "km/h" "mph" "ft/s" "knots" "Bft" "m/s"

The desired wind unit.

pressure
string (PressureUnit)
Enum: "hPa" "inHg" "mmHg" "mb"

The desired pressure unit.

solarRadiation
string (SolarRadiationUnit)
Value: "W/m²"

The desired solar radiation unit.

temperature
string (TemperatureUnit)
Enum: "°C" "°F"

The desired temperature unit.

leafTemperature
string (TemperatureUnit)
Enum: "°C" "°F"

The desired leaf temperature unit.

soilTemperature
string (TemperatureUnit)
Enum: "°C" "°F"

The desired soil temperature unit.

soilMoisture
string (SoilMoistureUnit)
Value: "cb"

The desired soil moisture unit.

humidity
string (HumidityUnit)
Value: "%"

The desired humidity unit.

evoTranspiration
string (RainUnit)
Enum: "in" "mm"

The desired evo transpiration unit.

Responses

Development server

http://localhost:8000/api/v1/live

Production server

https://harrystation.de:8000/api/v1/live

Gets the realtime wind chill, which automatically is converted to your passed unit. If no unit is passed the configured default unit will be used. Your api key needs read access.

Authorizations:
api_key
query Parameters
temperature
string (TemperatureUnit)
Enum: "°C" "°F"

The desired temperature unit.

from
string <date-time>
Example: from=2024-07-21T17:32:28Z

Inclusive start time of the interval

to
string <date-time>
Example: to=2024-07-21T17:32:28Z

Inclusive end time of the interval

rain
string (RainUnit)
Enum: "in" "mm"

The desired rain unit.

Get all records of the wind chill (in the specified interval)

Gets all records of the wind chill (in the specified interval). They get automatically converted into the desired units. If no units are passed the configured default units will be used. Your api key needs read access.

Authorizations:
api_key
query Parameters
from
string <date-time>
Example: from=2024-07-21T17:32:28Z

Inclusive start time of the interval

to
string <date-time>
Example: to=2024-07-21T17:32:28Z

Inclusive end time of the interval

temperature
string (TemperatureUnit)
Enum: "°C" "°F"

The desired temperature unit.

Responses

http://localhost:8000/api/v1/records/chill

config

Update the vant-environment configuration

Updates the vant-environment configuration. One needs an admin api key.

Authorizations:
api_key
Request Body schema: application/json
object (UnitSettings)
rainCollectorSize
string
Enum: "0.01in" "0.2mm" "0.1mm"
serialPath
string

The serial path the recorder uses to communicate with the weather station.

recordInterval
string

Interval the recorder sends realtime weather data to the vant api.

object

Configures in which interval records of a particular type of weather element are stored. You can specify multiple resolutions.

Responses

Development server

http://localhost:8000/api/v1/config

Production server

https://harrystation.de:8000/api/v1/config

Request samples

  • Payload
Content type
application/json
{
  • "units": {
    • "pressure": "hPa",
    • "rain": "in",
    • "solarRadiation": "W/m²",
    • "temperature": "°C",
    • "wind": "°C",
    • "soilMoisture": "cb",
    • "leafTemperature": "°C",
    • "soilTemperature": "°C",
    • "evoTranspiration": "in",
    • "humidity": "%"
    },
  • "rainCollectorSize": "0.01in",
  • "serialPath": "COM3",
  • "recordInterval": "1s",
  • "resolutions": {
    • "24h": { },
    • "7d": { },
    • "1m": { },
    • "archive": { }
    }
}

Response samples

  • 200
  • 400
  • 403
  • 500
Content type
application/json
{
  • "success": true
}

Generate a new api key

Returns a new api key. You need an admin api key to create new api keys.

Authorizations:
api_key
query Parameters
role
string
Enum: "read" "write" "readwrite" "admin"

The role (access privileges) of the generated api key.

Responses

Development server

http://localhost:8000/api/v1/config/generate-api-key

Production server

https://harrystation.de:8000/api/v1/config/generate-api-key

  • 400
  • 403
  • 500

highs-lows

Get alltime highs and lows

Gets the alltime highs and lows. They get automatically converted into the desired units. If no units are passed the configured default units will be used. Your api key needs read access.

Authorizations:
api_key
query Parameters
rain
string (RainUnit)
Enum: "in" "mm"

The desired rain unit.

wind
string (WindUnit)
Enum: "km/h" "mph" "ft/s" "knots" "Bft" "m/s"

The desired wind unit.

pressure
string (PressureUnit)
Enum: "hPa" "inHg" "mmHg" "mb"

The desired pressure unit.

solarRadiation
string (SolarRadiationUnit)
Value: "W/m²"

The desired solar radiation unit.

temperature
string (TemperatureUnit)
Enum: "°C" "°F"

The desired temperature unit.

leafTemperature
string (TemperatureUnit)
Enum: "°C" "°F"

The desired leaf temperature unit.

soilTemperature
string (TemperatureUnit)
Enum: "°C" "°F"

The desired soil temperature unit.

soilMoisture
string (SoilMoistureUnit)
Value: "cb"

The desired soil moisture unit.

humidity
string (HumidityUnit)
Value: "%"

The desired humidity unit.

evoTranspiration
string (RainUnit)
Enum: "in" "mm"

The desired evo transpiration unit.

Responses

Development server

http://localhost:8000/api/v1/highs-lows

Production server

https://harrystation.de:8000/api/v1/highs-lows

  • 400

climate

Get the measured long time average.

Gets the measured (not the configured) long time average. The data gets automatically converted into the desired units. If no units are passed the configured default units will be used. Your api key needs read access.

Authorizations:
api_key

Development server

http://localhost:8000/api/v1/climate

Production server

https://harrystation.de:8000/api/v1/climate
